SIMPLE: payoff
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: payoff
<hw>payoff</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>profit or gain from an
action; -- used broadly; <as>as, lots of effort with little
<ex>payoff</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>retribution, payback.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The act of giving or receiving money or other
valuable consideration as a bribe.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bribe.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>The money or item given as a bribe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>same as <er>compensation</er> 2.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> compensation, remuneration, recompense.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>The climax or final result of an event or endeavor;
the denouement of a narrative.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Payor</ent>⟦br⟧
